            "id": "31a3bf9a61324dfd9638e",
            "questionText": "An aerosol can contains a gas initially at $!$2.5 \\text{ atm} $!$ and $!$25^\\circ \\text{ C}$!$. If the can is placed in direct sunlight and the temperature of the gas increases to $!$50^\\circ \\text{ C}$!$, with the volume remaining constant and assuming the gas behaves ideally, calculate the final pressure in atmospheres.",
            "imageText": "",
            "steps": [
                {
                    "id": "a0868b0cf25d4613abb35",
                    "stepText": "Let's begin by identifying the gas law that relates pressure and temperature for a fixed volume. Please select the correct law from the options below.",
