        {
            "id": "b27a0960432146c2b070f",
            "questionText": "Given a tire with a fixed volume $!$V$!$ (in cubic meters), containing $!$n$!$ moles of air at an initial absolute temperature $!$T_1$!$ (in Kelvin) and an initial pressure $!$P_1$!$ (in Pascals), the air is heated so that its temperature increases to a final absolute temperature $!$T_2$!$ (in Kelvin). Using the ideal gas law, calculate the final pressure $!$P_2$!$ (in Pascals) inside the tire. Then, determine the pressure change $!$\\Delta P = P_2 - P_1$!$. Provide the numerical value of $!$\\Delta P$!$. (If any values such as $!$V$!$, $!$n$!$, $!$T_1$!$, $!$T_2$!$, or $!$P_1$!$ are missing, please supply them.)",
